comments: Finney-Smith (DAL) jumps towards and makes contact to Young's (ATL) lower body as he is landing on his jumpshot.
Dedmon (ATL) and Kleber (DAL) engage and separate during the rebound.
Dedmon's (ATL) hand slides off the ball and brushes Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) arm, but the contact is marginal and does not affect his ability to maintain control of the ball.
Huerter (ATL) makes incidental "high-five" contact with Kleber (DAL) after the release that does not affect his ability to follow through naturally on his  jump shot attempt.

As Wright (DAL) and Collins (ATL) disengage, Wright extends his leg and it is inconclusive based solely on the video whether Wright extends in an attempt to get around Collins or to intentionally kick the ball, which would be required for a kicked ball violation (not just foot-ball contact).
Collins (ATL) and Wright (DAL) engage and disengage during the rebound.
Collins (ATL) and Hardaway Jr. (DAL) connect as they attempt to get to the loose ball.
Kleber (DAL) is jumping A-B when Collins (ATL) is in his upward shooting motion toward the rim.
During the screen, Collins (ATL) and Curry (DAL) engage and disengage.
Finney-Smith (DAL) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact during the driving shot attempt by Young (ATL).
Finney-Smith (DAL) establishes himself in a screening position in Reddish's (ATL) path before the contact.
Dedmon (ATL) maintains a legal position at the start of Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) drive, and absorbs contact when Hardaway Jr. turns in toward the rim, and then they separate.
Dedmon (ATL) again maintains a legal guarding position at the end of Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) drive and absorbs the contact as he turns and drives toward the rim for a shot.
Collins (ATL) cleanly dislodges the ball from Finney-Smith (DAL) during the rebound attempt.
Replay Review determines the on-court ruling was overturned to Mavericks' ball.
Collins' (ATL) hand slides off Jackson's (DAL) back during the inbound play and the contact does not affect his FOM.
During the inbound, Dedmon (ATL) extends his arm slightly as Jackson (DAL) approaches, but does not affect his FOM as he cuts down the lane.
Finney-Smith (DAL) establishes himself in a screening position in Reddish's (ATL) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Finney-Smith (DAL) makes marginal contact to Dedmon (ATL) that does not affect his ability to maintain control of the ball.
Play under protest by the Mavericks.
Wright (DAL) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Young (ATL).
Collins (ATL) and Jackson (DAL) engage and separate during the inbound play.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) releases from the contact with Huerter (ATL) as he steps back into his jump shot attempt.
Collins (ATL) makes marginal contact with Wright (DAL) under the basket during the long rebound.
Finney-Smith (DAL) cleanly dislodges the ball from Dedmon (ATL) prior to making incidental contact.
